    <string name="terms_header">Terms of Use</string>
    <string name="terms_content">
        Welcome to StuShare - The learning resource sharing community.\n\n
        1. ACCEPTANCE OF TERMS\n
        By downloading, installing, and using StuShare, you agree to comply with these Terms of Use. If you do not agree, please do not use the app.\n\n
        2. INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY\n
        Any document you upload to StuShare must belong to you or you must have the legal right to share it. You are solely responsible for the copyright of the content you upload.\n\n
        3. CODE OF CONDUCT\n
        - Do not upload illegal, obscene, violent, or offensive content.\n
        - No spamming or unauthorized advertising.\n
        - Respect the community and other members.\n\n
        4. DISCLAIMER\n
        StuShare is an intermediary platform. We are not responsible for the accuracy or reliability of documents uploaded by users.\n\n
        5. VIOLATION HANDLING\n
        We reserve the right to remove any content that violates these terms and ban user accounts without prior notice.
    </string>

    <string name="privacy_header">Privacy Policy</string>
    <string name="privacy_content">
        StuShare is committed to protecting your privacy.\n\n
        1. INFORMATION COLLECTION\n
        We collect the following information to provide our services:\n
        - Personal Info: Name, Email, Profile Picture (upon login).\n
        - Usage Data: Download history, saved documents list.\n\n
        2. USE OF INFORMATION\n
        - Account management and user authentication.\n
        - Improving user experience and document recommendations.\n
        - Sending notifications about important updates.\n\n
        3. DATA SECURITY\n
        All your data is encrypted and stored securely on our servers. We implement advanced technical measures to prevent unauthorized access.\n\n
        4. DATA SHARING\n
        We commit NOT to sell, trade, or share your personal information with third parties, unless required by law enforcement agencies.\n\n
        5. YOUR RIGHTS\n
        You have the right to access, correct, or request the deletion of your personal data at any time via the Settings section in the app.
    </string>
